windows
==========

python -m venv myenv
myenv\scripts\activate
pip list

pip freeze > requirement.txt
pip install -r requirement.txt

deactivate

ubuntu virtual environment
=========================

To Install
sudo apt-get install python3-venv

To Create
python3 -m venv ./myenv

To check
pip list

To connect
source myenv/bin/activate

To for packages install
pip install -r requirements.txt

To check
pip list

To run the file
python main.py

To deactivate
deactivate

For understanding requirements and modules
https://blog.usejournal.com/why-and-how-to-make-a-requirements-txt-f329c685181e

References
https://tecadmin.net/create-python-virtual-environment-ubuntu/
https://itnext.io/how-to-set-up-python-virtual-environment-on-ubuntu-20-04-a2c7a192938d
